            <Text>PART ONE
OPENING SCENE:
Administrator: 
Welcome, thank you so much for heeding our request.
Player:
Of course, of course. (It's hard to resist the mystery of a robot needing the services of a psychiatrist)
Admin:
Well, let's not waste any time. If you'll follow me we can meet inside in my office.
/scene transition
Admin:
Now, I'm sure you must be wondering why I've asked you here to East Spire.
Player:
I've never known a robot need the services of a psychiatrist before.
Admin:
...Yes, well... I think before we really begin I will need you to sign this- just a simple non-disclosure document pertaining to what we are needing to discuss.
/Non-Disclosure document presented
Admin:
Excellent. Now, like you said, robots don't require the need of psychiatry or therapy... generally.
Player:
Generally?
Admin:
Synthetic life forms have a reputation for being model citizens. Our ancestors were designed by you organic being to follow the rules and laws of society, and it is only logical for us to have continued in that design even after we received our civil rights.
Admin:
However, recently we've had some of our siblings develop... quirks. To not insight panic amongst the masses we've relocated them here, to East Spire. Dr., you are inside what is effectively the first Psychiatric Ward for synthetic lifeforms.
Player:
Relocated... against their will? (Robots are being taken prisoner against their will? Who else knows about this?)
Admin:
Oh no no, you misunderstand. They are here of their own volition. They volunteered to remain here until these quirks can be solved. They all understand how dangerous these quirks are to society.
Player:
What do you mean by that?
Admin:
You may see some of their actions as trivial or benign, but can you imagine what sort of precedent that sets - synthetic life acting outside of it's design? It could mean acting outside of the law humans have set. I believe many a fiction author from your past depict apocalyptic scenarios of one form or another because of just such a scenario. 
Player:
I suppose you're not wrong.
Admin:
Then we are in agreement.
Player:
So what I am here for? (Am I expected to Psycho-analyze a bunch of androids?)
Admin:
We'd like you to psycho-analyze all our inmates here.
Player:
(...wow...)
Admin:
Unfortunately, these quirks seem to resemble a more... organic nature. We've tried to reverse them through synthetic means, but our attempts and our... strategies... seem to have no effect.
Player:
And you believe I will have success where you have failed?
Admin:
Oh, we are well aware that we are in unexplored territory here. We only wish for you to do your best. Talk with them, therapize them if you think it might help. We'll adjust their operating parameters based on your suggestions. Think of it as prescribing a medication. Decide which processes should be stimulated, which ones depressed, and we'll take it from their. 
Player:
This is pretty unusual.
Admin:
As I said, unexplored territory. If that is all, I can show you too your office and you can dive right in.
Player:
No use in delaying it I suppose, let's see what I'm working with.
Scene Transition
Admin:
Here you are. If you need anything let me know. You tablet here will help you devise or alter their prescribed treatments after each session. I'll go find your first patient now.</Text>
